==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stance
<hw>Stance</hw> <pr>(st⟦acr⟧ns)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>estance</ets>. See <er>Stanza</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
stanza.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A station; a position; a site.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Golf, Baseball)</fld> <def>The position of a
player's feet, relative to each other and to the ball, when he is making
a stroke or at bat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>the mental attitude, position, or approach a person
adopts in respect to something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stanch</ent>⟦br⟧
